      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that but i'm just looking for a straight answer on the biology of it. like, since melatonin is just a natural hormone and zolpidem is the heavy hitter, wouldnt the melatonin just act like a primer to help me fall asleep faster so the ambien can kick in more effectively? it doesnt seem like they would interact in a way that would actually hurt me, just make me sleep deeper. isn't it basically just doubling down on the same goal?",
