      "content": "While melatonin does signal your body to wind down, it does not work the same way as the potent sedative in Ambien and may not actually \"prime\" it for faster onset. Taking them simultaneously can compound your central nervous system suppression, increasing the risk of severe side effects like respiratory depression, complex sleep behaviors, or severe brain fog rather than simply improving sleep depth. Because safety depends on individual factors like your metabolism and current dosage, it is best to rely on your doctor's specific guidance rather than assuming the combination is safe due to their shared goal.",
